 The Kaduna State Government, Malam Nasir El-Rufai has deployed new technology to facilitate data collection on rising cases of malnutrition to enable it to tackle the challenge effectively. The mobile District Health Information System, provided with support from Alive and Thrive, an NGO, would be deployed to 270 rural health facilities. Hamza-Ibrahim Ikara,  Deputy Director, State  Primary Healthcare Development Agency, said the equipment was deployed as part of a strategic initiative to get accurate data on malnutrition. Continue reading Kaduna Govt. inaugurate data collection system on malnutrition at Vanguard News. Source: Vanguard